      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCOTT GREYSCALE (1) was favourite last start and led all the way, scoring by 3 lengths (21.97) at Shepparton in a Grade 5 over 390m. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from three starts. Great chance to get the job done again. HARD STYLE ROBBO (2) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Myall Mate (24.33) in a Special conditions Veteran race. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form from his last run stacks up well. Must be included in calculations. HARLOW'S BOY (3) quickly into stride to win over the 425m at this track two runs back then raced on speed again when finishing second at Horsham last start. Leading player again. PIEBALD (5) must be included in calculations.",
